When I confronted them about it, Brooke rolled her eyes and said maybe Chloe posted them herself for attention. Madison just stood there smirking like it was all some big joke. That night, I told my wife we needed to put a lock on Chloe's door. She flipped out, saying I was being paranoid and that it would hurt Jake's feelings if we didn't trust his daughters. She said family doesn't lock doors against family, and I was overreacting to normal teenage drama. But I wasn't backing down. The next morning, I went to Home Depot and bought a doorknob with a key lock. I installed it myself while everyone was out of the house and gave Chloe the only two keys. When Jake saw it that evening, he lost his mind. He started yelling about how I was treating his daughters like criminals and how dare I make them feel unwelcome in our house. My wife was standing behind him, nodding along like I was the bad guy here. I looked him dead in the eye and said, the lock stays until you and your daughters find somewhere else to live. He asked what that was supposed to mean, and I told him exactly what I meant. His daughters have been stealing from Chloe, going through her private stuff, and now they're cyberbullying her online. Get your things and call your mom to pick you up. She started getting that bratty tone. Riley invited me over. You can't just kick me out for no reason. I heard what you said about me.

That bridesmaid who got hot and my best friend tried to kick me out of her wedding because of it. When Riley asked me to be her maid of honor, I cried. We've been best friends since sophomore year of college. The kind of friends who knew each other's coffee orders and Netflix passwords. She'd always been the gorgeous one, the one guys noticed first when we walked into bars. I was the funny sidekick who made everyone laugh when conversations got awkward. I was fine with it. That was just our thing. She got engaged Connor in February and the wedding was set for October, eight months away. When she handed me the bridesmaid dress options at her apartment, she hesitated before saying, so these run pretty small. The designer only goes up to a size 16 and you like an 18 or 20, right? She said it so casually like she was commenting on the weather. Maybe we could get you a personal trainer as an early birthday gift. I know this amazing guy named Dominic who works at APEX Fitness downtown, got my cousin Rachel into crazy good shape. I felt my face get hot, but I smiled and said sure. She venmoed me $800 that night with a note for Dominic, you're gonna look so good. I met Dominic the next Monday. He was brutal. Six days a week, 5:00am full body torture sessions that left me barely able to walk to my car. He put Me on 1,400 calories a day, mostly grilled protein and vegetables. No alcohol, no, no sugar, no excuses. I started tracking everything in this app called my plate. I cancelled plans so I could meal prep. I stopped going to happy hours. My co workers asked if I was okay because I turned down birthday cake three times. But something clicked. For the first time in my life, I felt in control. By June, I'd lost 40 pounds. By September, I'd lost 70. My face had cheekbone. My collarbone showed. I bought jeans in a size 6, a size I'd never even touched in a store before. I felt like I'd unlocked a secret level of life I didn't know existed two weeks before.

Parents who have genuinely stopped loving their child. What happened when my 18 year old daughter Cassie dropped out of nursing school to become an only fans model? Her father and I were devastated. We had spent over six figures to put her through her first two years of nursing school just for her to drop out. But after several conversations with her, we decided to put everything behind us and continue supporting her. Eventually she converted her room into a little filming studio and my husband and I did our best to keep our younger 14 year old daughter Junah safe. Over the years, Cassie became quite popular on that site and the noises from her room were ungodly. As bad as we wanted her to move out, we didn't have the guts to tell her to leave. Kept thinking that she might change and go back to school. But we didn't realize how wrong we were until it was too late. When Juno was in her senior year of high school and we urged her to start sending out college apps. It caught my husband and I by great surprise when Juno said she wasn't planning on going to college. She said she wanted to make easy money just like Cassie. She didn't think it was fair to have to go to college and then look for a dumb corporate job. When her sister was given the easy pass and was working literally from her bed, I cried. And begged her to think it through. If she became a mattress actress, there would be no going back. But she didn't care. The more I begged, the more she resented me. I was drinking wine one night, rethinking my entire life, when Junia came down the stairs and I asked her to sit with me. I begged her to please just explain why she wanted to do this. She admitted to Cassie talking to her about this ever.

He seemed to think that as long as he told me the facts, he'd done his part. My phone buzzed again, booked us a table at that restaurant. You love dinner tonight. That was his classic move, an explanation followed by a treat. Whether I accepted his peace offering or not, he would consider the matter closed as long as he felt he'd explained himself. I was expected to drop it. So many times I tried to push, to scream that we needed to actually talk things through, but the look in his eyes always said the same. He just didn't get it. Saw me as a petulant child throwing a tantrum. And so more often than not, I was the one who swallowed my hurt, plastering on a smile and playing the part of the mature, understanding girlfriend just to please him. I sounds good. Kobe could handle spicy food, but he didn't enjoy it. He would never suggest that place on his own. I should have been thrilled. Instead, all I felt was a profound emptiness. Knew better than to expect Kobe to pick me up, so I called a car myself. And once again, my instincts were right. On the way to the Guizuan restaurant, we passed by his office building and there he was. I watched from my car window as Kobe, a faint smile on his. I held Lola's head with his hand as she slipped into the passenger seat of his car. A cold Certainty washed over me. I unlocked my phone. Sure enough, a series of new messages were there. Lola's joining us for dinner. She's been working so hard lately, hasn't had a decent meal in days. She he doesn't like spicy food. We'll go to that situ one place another time, I promise. I booked a different restaurant, sending you the new address now. I switched off the screen and told the driver to continue to the original destination. Kobe had already cancelled our reservation, so I had to wait in line. The place was packed. It took an hour before I was seated. My phone buzzed incessantly in my purse, but I ignored it, focusing only on the food. The spice was so authentic it brought tears to my eyes, but it was a good burn, a cleansing one. Only after I paid the Bill did I finally take out my phone. As I suspected, it was flooded with over a dozen missed calls and messages from him. Are you there yet? Are you throwing a fit again? I told you I take you next time. Lola has a sensitive stomach. She can't eat spicy food. You're practically her sister in law. Could you be a little more understanding now? She feels so guilty she can't even eat. Get over here now. The same old script. It was more than we had texted each other in the last month combined. On the way home, I found myself wondering what had Made me fall for Kobe in the first place. I think it was that rainy afternoon. He, I was trying to launch his startup and had just been rejected by an investor for the 20th time. My boss had just sent back my design draft for the 35th revision. We both ducked into the same coffee shop to escape a sudden thunderstorm and just, we started talking. It was awkward at first. Just, just small talk to fill the silence. But by the time the rain stopped, we had click. After that, getting together felt like the most natural thing in the world. Never believed in love at first sight. It always seemed too shallow. An emotion without foundation, destined to fade as quickly as it appeared. Yet for six years with Kobe.

I planned an international travel without my children. I've got two kids, 16 and 14 now. When me and their mom split up six years ago, we did the whole 50 50 thing, week on, week off. It was fine. The kids adjusted. I had them half the time, she had them half the time. Nobody was complaining. Then 4 years ago, my ex got remarried. Her new husband convinced her to go back to court and fight for more custody. I still don't know why. Maybe he wanted to play stepdad of the year. Maybe they just wanted child support money. Whatever the reason, she filed. I had to hire a lawyer, then another one. When the first guy turned out to be useless, 4 years of court dates, mediations, evaluations, therapy sessions for the kids. The Bill kept climbing. By the time we finally went to trial last spring, I had spent $165,000. That was everything I had saved. My retirement fund, gone. The money I was putting away for the kids college, gone. Every dollar I scraped together from overtime and side jobs, gone. My ex didn't pay a cent. Her dad is loaded and he covered all her legal fees. Must be nice. The court made the kids talk to a therapist. The older one, my 16 year old, told them straight up that they wanted to live with mom full time and only see me every other weekend. The younger one said they still wanted 50. 50 at first. Then a few weeks later they changed their mind and said maybe 70, 30 with mom would be better. Said they just wanted the court stuff to be over. I get it. Four years is a long time for kids to deal with that, but it still hurt. We went to trial in June. My lawyer actually did a good job, presented everything properly, pointed out that there was no reason to change custody, that I've been a good parent the whole time, didn't matter. The judge said that given their ages, the kids'preference was the most important factor and she wasn't going to split them up because that would damage their sibling bond or whatever. So that's how I ended up with every other weekend four years and $165,000 later, I get to see my kids four days a month. My wife and I needed something to look forward to after all that. Her sister suggested we do a trip with her and her husband and some of their friends. Nine days in Spain and France, Barcelona, Madrid, Paris. We've been talking about doing something like this for years but never actually pulled the trigger. They picked the dates in October. We all booked tickets, got an Airbnb in Barcelona and hotel rooms in Madrid and Paris. My wife's sister's family was bringing their 15 year old son. We planned hiking, museums, trying actual Spanish food, all of it. The kids came over for their Weekend in September, they were in the kitchen while I was making dinner and my younger one saw the tickets printed out on the counter. They picked it up and said, what's this? I told them it was for a trip we had planned. My older one looked over their shoulder and said, Spain? You're going to Spain? I said, yes. They both started talking at once, when are you going? How long can we come? Why didn't you tell us? I explained that this was something me and my wife planned with her family, that we've been saving up for it and it was already booked. My younger one said, but we wanna go.

Did your family realise you weren't stupid? My family introduces me to people as mentally slow because I have a stutter. My dad will pull new people aside and whisper. She has severe difficulties. Just smile and nod when she tries to talk. But my sister's engagement party was a new level of humiliation. The entire extended family was there at this upscale restaurant. She'd rented out 50 guests, including her fiance's family, who I'd never met before. The moment I walked in, my mom rushed over to my sister's future in laws. I watched her do the routine. The concerned face, the lowered voice, the pitying headshake. That's our other daughter. She's just be patient if she tries to communicate. The fiance's mother put her hand over her heart and nodded sympathetically when I approached their table to introduce myself. I started to say hello, I'm. But my dad immediately stepped in front of me. She gets overwhelmed. We've been working on greetings for years. He turned to me and spoke loudly and slowly. Can you wave hello? Remember how we practiced? Entire table looked at me with those horrible pity smiles. My brother thought this was the perfect time for his favorite party trick. Watch this. He announced to a group of cousins, hey, Gia, tell everyone what you do for work. Before I could even open my mouth, he answered for me. She thinks she's a lawyer. Isn't that adorable? Everyone laughed when I pulled out my Phone to show everyone something. My mom snatched it away. No phone, sweetie. You know they confuse you. She handed me a coloring book instead, an actual coloring book she kept in her purse here. This is a simpler task than speaking. I actually am a lawyer and I've won 47 murder cases as a prosecutor. My aunt was explaining to the fiance's family how brave my parents were. They could have institutionalized her, but they keep her at home. Saints, really. She can barely string two words together without crying. I tried to speak up. I need to tell you, but my sister cut me off. She's trying to say she needs the bathroom. Don't worry, she can go by herself now. We're so proud of her progress. I patted my head like I was a puppy. My cousin, who failed the bar exam three times, was loudly telling everyone how sad it was that I'd never experienced real life. He said she keeps telling people she works at the courthouse. Poor thing. Probably saw it on TV and got confused. Imagine her trying to be a lawyer. He did a cruel impression. Ye, ye, ye, your honor, I rest my case. Everyone roared with laughter. The waiter came to take dessert orders. When he asked me what I'd like, my mom answered for me, she'll have vanilla ice cream, one scoop. She makes a mess with more than that. Then she asked the waiter for a bib, a Bib. The waiter looked confused but brought one anyway. My phone was buzzing constantly in my mom's purse. I, I could see it lighting up with call after call. Mom noticed and turned it off completely. Probably spam calls she signs up for, things she doesn't understand. That's when the restaurant door burst open. Three police officers walked in, scanning the room urgently. Everyone went silent. My dad stood up nervously. Is there a problem?

Did your family realise you weren't stupid? My family introduces me to people as mentally slow because I have a stutter. My dad will pull new people aside and whisper. She has severe difficulties. Just smile and nod when she tries to talk. But my sister's engagement party was a new level of humiliation. The entire extended family was there at this upscale restaurant. She'd rented out 50 guests, including her fiance's family, who I'd never met before. The moment I walked in, my mom rushed over to my sister's future in laws. I watched her do the routine. The concerned face, the lowered voice, the pitying headshake. That's our other daughter. She's just be patient if she tries to communicate. The fiance's mother put her hand over her heart and nodded sympathetically when I approached their table to introduce myself. I started to say hello, I'm. But my dad immediately stepped in front of me. She gets overwhelmed. We've been working on greetings for years. He turned to me and spoke loudly and slowly. Can you wave hello? Remember how we practiced? Entire table looked at me with those horrible pity smiles. My brother thought this was the perfect time for his favorite party trick. Watch this. He announced to a group of cousins, hey, Gia, tell everyone what you do for work. Before I could even open my mouth, he answered for me. She thinks she's a lawyer. Isn't that adorable? Everyone laughed when I pulled out my Phone to show everyone something. My mom snatched it away. No phone, sweetie. You know they confuse you. She handed me a coloring book instead, an actual coloring book she kept in her purse here. This is a simpler task than speaking. I actually am a lawyer and I've won 47 murder cases as a prosecutor. My aunt was explaining to the fiance's family how brave my parents were. They could have institutionalized her, but they keep her at home. Saints, really. She can barely string two words together without crying. I tried to speak up. I need to tell you, but my sister cut me off. She's trying to say she needs the bathroom. Don't worry, she can go by herself now. We're so proud of her progress. I patted my head like I was a puppy. My cousin, who failed the bar exam three times, was loudly telling everyone how sad it was that I'd never experienced real life. He said she keeps telling people she works at the courthouse. Poor thing. Probably saw it on TV and got confused. Imagine her trying to be a lawyer. He did a cruel impression. Ye, ye, ye, your honor, I rest my case. Everyone roared with laughter. The waiter came to take dessert orders. When he asked me what I'd like, my mom answered for me, she'll have vanilla ice cream, one scoop. She makes a mess with more than that. Then she asked the waiter for a bib, a Bib. The waiter looked confused but brought one anyway. My phone was buzzing constantly in my mom's purse. I, I could see it lighting up with call after call. Mom noticed and turned it off completely. Probably spam calls she signs up for, things she doesn't understand. That's when the restaurant door burst open. Three police officers walked in, scanning the room urgently. Everyone went silent. My dad stood up nervously. Is there a problem?

Her new husband convinced her to go back to court and fight for more custody. I still don't know why. Maybe he wanted to play stepdad of the year. Maybe they just wanted child support money. Whatever the reason, she filed. I had to hire a lawyer. Then another one when the first guy turned out to be useless. Four years of court dates, mediations, evaluations, therapy sessions for the kids. Bill kept climbing. By the time we finally went to trial last spring, I had spent $165,000. That was everything I had saved. My retirement fund, gone. The money I was putting away for the kids, college, gone. Every dollar I scraped together from overtime and side jobs, gone. My ex didn't pay a cent. Her dad is loaded and he covered all her legal fees. Must be nice. The court made the kids talk to a therapist. The older one, my 16 year old, told them straight up that they wanted to live with mom full time and only see me every other weekend. The younger one said they still wanted fifty Fifty at first. Then a few weeks later, they changed their mind and said maybe 70 30 with mom would be better. Said they just wanted the court stuff to be over. I get it. Four years is a long time for kids to deal with that. But it still hurt. We went to trial in June. My lawyer actually did a good job. Presented everything properly. Pointed out that there was no reason to change custody, that I'd been a good parent the whole time, didn't matter. The judge said that given their ages, the kids preference was the most important factor. And she wasn't going to split them up because that would damage their sibling bond or whatever. So that's how I ended up with every other weekend. Four years and $165,000 later, I get to see my kids four days a month. My wife and I needed something to look forward to after all that. Her sister suggested we do a trip with her and her husband and some of their friends. Nine days in Spain and France. Barcelona, Madrid, Paris. We've been talking about doing something like this for years, but never actually pulled the trigger. They picked the dates in October. We all booked tickets, got an Airbnb in Barcelona and hotel rooms in Madrid and Paris. My wife's sister's family was bringing their 15 year old son. We planned hiking, museums, trying actual Spanish food, all of it. The kids came over for their Weekend in September. They were in the kitchen while I was making dinner and my younger one saw the tickets printed out on the counter. They picked it up and said, what's this? I told them it was for a trip we had planned. My older one looked over their shoulder and said, Spain. You're going to Spain? I said, yes. They both started talking at once. When are you going? How long can we come? Why didn't you tell us? I explained that this was something me and my wife planned with her family, that we'd been saving up for it and it was already booked. My younger one said, but we wanna go.

Did your family realise you weren't stupid? My family introduces me to people as mentally slow because I have a stutter. My dad will pull new people aside and whisper, she has severe difficulties. Just smile and nod when she tries to talk. But my sister's engagement party was a new level of humiliation. The entire extended family was there at this upscale restaurant. She'd rented out 50 guests, including her fiance's family, who I'd never met before. The moment I walked in, my mom rushed over to my sister's future in laws. I watched her do the routine. The concerned face, the lowered voice, the pitying head shake. That's our other daughter. She's just be patient. If she tries to communicate. The fiance's mother put her hand over her heart and nodded sympathetically when I approached their table to introduce myself. I started to say, hello, I'm. But my dad immediately stepped in front of me. She gets overwhelmed. We've been working on greetings for years. He turned to me and spoke loudly and slowly. Can you wave hello? Remember how we practiced? Entire table looked at me with those horrible pity smiles. My brother thought this was the perfect time for his favorite party trick. Watch this, he announced to a group of cousins. Hey, Gia, tell everyone what you do for work. Before I could even open my mouth, he answered for me. She thinks she's a lawyer. Isn't that adorable? Everyone laughed when I pulled out My phone. To show everyone something. My mom snatched it away. No phone, sweetie. You know they confuse you. She handed me a coloring book instead. An actual coloring book she kept in her purse. Here. This is a simpler task than speaking. I actually am a lawyer, and I've won 47 murder cases as a prosecutor. My aunt was explaining to the fiance's family how brave my parents were. They could have institutionalized her, but they keep her at home. Saints, really. She can barely string two words together without crying. I tried to speak up. I need to tell you, but my sister cut me off. She's trying to say she needs the bathroom. Don't worry. She can go by herself now. We're so proud of her progress. I patted my head like I was a puppy. My cousin, who failed the bar exam three times, was loudly telling everyone how sad it was that I'd never experienced real life. He said, she keeps telling people she works at the courthouse. Poor thing. Probably saw it on TV and got confused. Imagine her trying to be a lawyer. He did a cruel impression. Ye, ye, ye! Your honor, I rest my case. Everyone roared with laughter. The waiter came to take dessert orders. When he asked me what I'd like, my mom answered for me, she'll have vanilla ice cream. One scoop. She makes a mess with more than that. Then she asked the waiter for a bib. A bib. The waiter looked confused, but brought one anyway. My phone was buzzing constantly in my mom's purse. I, I could see it lighting up with call after call. Mom noticed and turned it off completely. Probably spam calls. She signs up for things she doesn't understand. That's when the restaurant door burst open. Three police officers walked in, scanning the room urgently. Everyone went silent. My dad stood up nervously. Is there a problem

My girlfriend slept with her celebrity crush for 3 years. She talked about this indie streamer, non stop, 12,000 followers, plays retro games in his parents basement, barely famous. She joke, if I ever met him, you know the deal. And I'd laugh it off like everyone does with celebrity crushes. I'd say, yeah, mine's Margo Robbie. And we both laugh. Never once thought she was serious. Last month he announced a meet and greet tour, five cities, 50 tickets each. When he added our city to the lineup, she lost her mind, showed me the announcement at breakfast, already planning to go. Tickets were $200 each. She just spent $800 fixing her car's transmission and was completely broke. She didn't directly ask me to pay, just kept mentioning it. Only 50 tickets, they'll sell out so fast. Then she'd sigh and say, guess I'll have to skip. I felt terrible watching her disappointed. So I picked up overtime shifts at the warehouse, double shifts on weekends, came home exhausted, saved up $250 to cover the tip get and give her some extra for parking and food. Her face when I gave her the money made it worth it. She actually cried, kissed me, said I was the best boyfriend ever, that she didn't deserve me. I felt like a hero. The meet and greet was on a Saturday. She left at four PM, said it started at six PM but she wanted to be early, texted me at 7:30. Saying it was amazing he was even cooler in person. Then nothing. Midnight, no response. 1:00am, nothing. I called twice, straight to voicemail. At 2:00am, I was pacing our apartment thinking she got in an accident. Finally texted her best friend, Alexa, asking if she'd heard from her. Alexa said, isn't she with you? She walked in at 3:00am. I was furious and relieved. She looked different. Makeup smudged, wearing a hoodie I'd never seen, hair messy. I asked where she'd been and she said, we all went to this diner. After my phone died, something felt wrong, but I was too tired to push. We went to bed. Sunday morning, her phone kept buzzing. Constant notifications she was in the shower. To continue, tap the arrow in the bottom right corner and copy the link and tap the CapCut icon in the bottom left. Finally click the red button. When I pulled out the tampon in front of her, she actually gagged. We need to admit you, she said, covering her mouth. Hospital day 1 IV.

Surgeon looked me dead in the eye and said you can only save one, your mother or your son. I whispered, save the one who didn't lie to me. My mother called me crying at 2:00am said she needed emergency surgery. Her appendix, life or death. I rushed to the hospital in 20 minutes. When I got there, the nurse looked confused. Used your mother, sir, you already checked in a family member tonight. That's when my stomach dropped. Turns out my 15 year old son Jake was already there. Different floor, motorcycle accident on his way home from a study group. Except Jake doesn't own a motorcycle and his study group ended at eight PM I called his friend's mom to confirm they'd left the library together. At 7:30 I found Jake in the er, conscious but banged up pretty bad. Road rash down his left arm, possible internal bleeding. His phone was shattered, the table next to him. Dad, I can explain, he started, but the tears came too fast. Where were you, I asked, trying to stay calm. I was just riding around the neighborhood. I'm sorry. I'm so sorry. On what motorcycle, Jake? We don't have a motorcycle. He wouldn't answer. Just kept crying and saying sorry over and over. Then I got the call about my mother. Same hospital, two floors up, actually did need emergency surgery, appendicitis. That turned into a rupture. I spent the next hour running between floors. My son who'd been Lying to me, my mother who raised me. That's when the surgeon found me in the hallway. Doctor Chen looked exhausted. Mr Martinez, we have a serious problem. Both of them need did immediate surgery. Both had the same rare blood type, AB negative. The hospital only had enough units for one emergency procedure tonight. The nearest hospital with more AB negative is 2 hours away, doctor, and said we have to airlift it. Your mother's appendix could rupture completely. In that time. Your son's internal bleeding could get worse. So I have to choose. I'm sorry. Yes. I stood there frozen. What kind of choice is that, your mother or your son? My mother kept saying, choose me. I raised you. I gave you life. You owe me this. Jake just kept his eyes closed, wouldn't look at me. The tears rolling down his face. Then my mom's friend Carol showed up. I didn't even know she was in town. Oh, honey, this is terrible, Carol said, hugging my mom. First Vegas, now this. You can't catch a break. I looked at her. Vegas. Yeah. Last weekend was such a blast. Remember when we, my mother cut her off fast, Carol. Not now. But I was already processing it. Last weekend, my mother told me she was visiting her sister Linda in Phoenix. Linda's been sick, needed help around the house. I called Linda that Sunday to check in. She said mom hadn't visited in months. You were in Vegas. I asked my mother. We'll talk about this later, sweetheart. I'm about to have surgery. Something felt wrong, really wrong. I walked back down to Jake's room, started looking around his backpack.

I got banged by all black guys. I ended up in a weekend long gang bang with all black guys. It started late Friday evening and I was dropped off at home late Sunday night by a loud carload of black guys in our upper middle class Lily white neighborhood. Definitely woke up some neighbors. I was partially dressed, dripping their milk loads everywhere, missing an expensive bra and one shoe. I was barely able to walk from all the meat that I took and Coca Cola, not the drink. And I had told my husband I was going out for a few hours Friday evening. I hadn't called him at all and got dropped off in that shape all messed up. I have no idea how many guys I was with, but it was a lot. And I took their loads multiple times throughout the weekend. They all took me any type of way that they wanted and I just let it happened. I loved the thrill and attention I was getting from all of them. My diaphragm had been removed Sometime Friday night while they were rubbing Coca Cola on my kitty cat. Wow. If you've never tried it and I never saw it again, this was hands down the most truly exciting thing I have ever done. But it also almost destroyed my marriage. A lot of videos of that weekend got leaked and my husband came across some of them. When he confronted me, he was really angry. He got really emotional and said that I lost his trust. For a few minutes, I didn't really know what to say. I had hope that no one was recording. I was wrong. I tried to reason with him and give him some comfort, but he rejected me every time. He didn't talk to me for a whole week. Eventually, we talked about what happened. I apologized and we worked it out. I only did it that one time. Why does he have to be so insecure?

His dad wants to try me before the wedding. Two nights before my wedding, Marcus and I were sitting on our apartment floor folding programs and sipping wine. When he said so casually, tomorrow night, my father needs to examine you. I blinked. Sorry, what? He looked at me like I'd forgotten the salad for dinner. It's a family tradition. My brothers and Uncle Roberto will be there, too. Just takes a few minutes. I laughed, because what else do you do when someone says something that insane? But Marcus wasn't laughing. His face stayed dead serious. He reached for my hand, started rubbing circles in my palm like he always did to calm me. It's how we make sure the bride is pure, he said. I couldn't wrap my head around it. We were sitting in our candlelit apartment, R S V P. Cards and neat stacks. Our honeymoon to Santorini already booked. And now he wanted his dad to inspect me with witnesses. I asked if his mom had done it. He nodded. Every woman who marries into the Castano family does. My mom, Maria, all my cousin's wives. It proves your love, shows your honest. That was the moment the warmth I'd felt from his family flipped into something colder than ice. His mom, the woman who comforted me when my grandma died, who taught me how to make her Sunday sauce, she went through this. I yanked my hand away. No, that's not happening. He looked Crushed like I just told him I cheated on him or something. You don't understand, he said. It's not some violation. It. It's tradition. Verification. Just five minutes, then it's done. Now I understood why he'd insisted we wait. I thought it was sweet. Turned out it was about preserving me like some ancient relic so I could be verified by his dad like a sealed package. I can't, I whispered. I grabbed my keys and left, drove through pouring rain to my best friend's apartment, sobbing, mascara running down my dress. She opened the door. I collapsed into her arms and choked out, he wants his dad to check me. She poured wine I couldn't drink and just held my hand while I fell asleep on her couch. The next morning, I went back to our place. I don't know why. Maybe to hear him say it was all some stupid joke. What I found was Marcus crying at the table, surrounded by wedding junk. If you loved me, you'd protect me from this, I said. And he slapped me. Neither of us expected it. His face changed instantly, like he couldn't believe he'd done it. I touched my cheek, set the ring on the counter, and left. Three days later, he showed up at my friend's door, pale, shaking. Said, I hit you to save your life. I stared. Excuse me, he whispered. It's not about

I let my girlfriend's little sister rub my hot dog. Last night. When my girlfriend left, I thought I was alone at her house. So I decided to watch some corn videos on the TV. And I started rubbing my hot dog. I think it had been about 15 minutes. I had watched a couple of videos, flicking through them, trying to find the right one. I needed the perfect video because I wanted to surprise my girlfriend with my load on her panties. Then I finally found it, but before I could click on it, my girlfriend's sister charged in. She didn't knock and even say anything, just came straight in. I panicked and quickly turned off the TV, forgetting that my hot dog was hanging out full, hard and close to exploding. Lucy, my girlfriend's little sister, stood there, didn't even say anything, just covered her mouth with her hand. I wanted to apologize to her, but before I could say anything, she wanted to make a deal with me. Let me rub your huge black hot dog and I won't tell anyone what has happened. My heart stopped and I didn't know what to, to do. But because I took so long to reply, Lucy just came to me and started rubbing it. I started moaning while she was giggling. And after 30 seconds, I milked, but not where I originally wanted to. She put her face right in the line and took my load as I Was just standing there. She looked at me in the eyes with her face covered in my load and thanked me for the experience. She then left and I haven't spoken to her since. Now I am worried that she will tell anyone.

I shot up and shook Jenny awake. Someone's stealing our money. What? Get up. Check your purse for your cards. Had the bank on speaker while throwing on pants. Cancel the card. Stop them. We're trying, sir, but they have your pin. They're at the daily limit now. Moving to your savings. How do they have my pin? Jenny was dumping her purse. My card's gone. My whole wallet's gone. Mine, too. I said checking my jeans. The ATM camera shows a young male, approximately 17 to 20. The bank said we need to get there now. We ran to the garage. Both cars, cars were there, but Jenny's keys were missing. They took my keys, too. We jumped in my car. I was doing 60 in a residential zone. Jenny was on with 9, 1, 1. Someone's robbing us at the chase at. They have our cards and pins. Units responding. The bank called back. They're trying the credit cards now at the ATM. How much have they gotten? 8,000 from checking and savings combined. Hit the daily limits. Are they still there? Camera shows them walking to a car now. Black Toyota Corolla. That's my car. Jenny screamed, they stole my car. We pulled into the bank as police arrived. My car was gone. The ATM screen Was still showing our gutted account balance. Did you see their face? The cop asked. Our daughter Mackenzie, 16, who was supposed to be asleep in her room. I called her phone straight to voicemail. We raced home. Her bedroom window was open, bed stuffed with pillows, her backpack on, half her clothes missing.

voice_to_text: He told me to put my hand over the flame to test my loyalty. I did it without flinching. Satisfied, he turned away to answer a call. He kept talking and forgot I was still burning. By the time he looked back, my whole arm was on fire. He just laughed because I'm not human. I'm a robot. He bought for $180,000 the real human touch. Programmed to fulfill his every demand. The moment I was powered on, I was coded to love him. Love Link established. Hey, you! That day, Matt took me to a party at his friend's villa. On the way, I noticed the GPS didn't show this road. Matt said it was private property. I didn't think much of it. At the entrance, I suddenly froze. I was afraid his friends wouldn't like me. I still didn't know I was just a robot. I just wanted to get along with them. Matt said a few comforting words. I gathered my courage and followed him. Inside, his friends were warm and welcoming. The villa owner, Jack, seemed especially impressed. He said Matt had found such a perfect girlfriend. But I caught a hint of greed in his eyes. That night, everyone drank and danced. The mood was great. No one knew a terrible scheme was brewing. The next day, everyone planned to sunbathe by the lake. But Matt said he had something to do and told me to go ahead. I did as he said. When I Got there. Only Jack was waiting. Felt uneasy. But he was the host, so I couldn't just leave. I sat on the lounge chair next to him. He handed me sunscreen and asked me to rub it on his back. Reluctantly, I stepped forward. Then he dropped the act. He said Matt had agreed to lend me to him for a day. He lunged at me. I fought back with everything I had. In desperation, I pulled out the small knife from my pocket. I struck him down. I went back to the villa covered in blood. Everyone froze. Robots should never be able to harm humans. Matt immediately shut me down. When I powered back on, I was tied up tight. I broke down completely. Matt finally told me the truth. I'm a robot. I couldn't believe it. Iris, do you know any foreign languages? My system supports over a dozen languages. I had no idea I wasn't human. After I calmed down, I realized something. I didn't even care. I just wanted to live with Matt like before. Then Jack's girlfriend called Matt away. Everything that happened was all part of their plan. They opened Jack's safe. Inside was $12 million in cash. Everyone there would split it. The reason I could break the rule against harming humans. Matt had hacked my programming. Once they restored everything, they could pin all the blame on me. They had already called the cops. They were just waiting for the police to Take me away. But I didn't know something. I had amplified my hearing and caught every word. I tipped over the chair and grabbed the knife from under the table. I cut the ropes and escaped into the woods. I also took Matt's phone. If I could access the program that controls me, I can max out my intelligence to 100%. Now it's my turn to fight back.

voice_to_text: To claim a ten billion dollar inheritance, this woman had just pushed her own sister off a towering cliff, perfectly staging the scene to look like suicide. She quickly pulled out her phone and began recording. Standing before the camera, she declared solemnly, if you find a body at the bottom of the cliff near my house, know that it's me. The moment she finished, she uploaded the clip to social media. She turned to glance at her sister one last time, but then she spotted a fake leg lying near the cliff edge. When she picked it up and looked down, she saw her sister's motionless body below and realized, horrified, that her sister was disabled. She had worked so hard to make the corpse look like her own, and now her entire plan was falling apart. Panicking, she remembered the video was still uploading. Thankfully, the signal was weak. Just as the upload neared completion, she switched her phone into airplane mode. After a moment frantic thinking, she hurried down the cliff, screaming, no! You're in my place! Everyone will know you're not me! How am I supposed to cover this up? While spiraling in fear, noticed a railway line nearby and a train rapidly approaching. She glanced at her own two healthy legs and a new scheme formed instantly. If she placed the fake leg on the track, it would appear as though the train had run over her sister. No one would ever guess her sister Had a disability. She set the fake leg carefully on the rail and hid behind a massive boulder. Moments later, the train roared past.

I looked at the pizza in my hand. I noticed that the toppings had been eaten by someone from the upper level. So I thought about taking someone else's food. However, as soon as I picked up a piece of chicken wing, Tony from the upper level stopped me, told me I could only eat my own food. This was the rule of the loyalists because if someone steals food, it means the people below will go hungry. I explained that my pizza had been eaten by someone else. Tony said they would solve the problem for me, and he told me not to break the rules. If I insisted on stealing someone else's food, I would be punished by the loyalists. I didn't want to hear their explanation. I just wanted to compensate myself immediately. But then my cellmate Jenny stopped me. She gave me her croquette to eat, so I finally put the chicken wing back. The next day, we heard fighting from upstairs. Four members from the 19th and 20th floors came down to the 21st floor to punish the one who stole my pizza. But the four of them couldn't even beat the opponent. This meant the thief had strong combat abilities. Tony from upstairs told me that if they couldn't beat that person, Jenny and I would need to prepare for a fight. Hearing this, I immediately gave up and lied, saying I never fought. But as soon as I finished speaking, the platform arrived. Upstairs, Tony and Laura immediately started fighting. Seeing this, Jenny quickly lifted the mattress, then took out an iron bar from the bed frame to prepare for the enemy. When the platform came down, I was stunned. I saw a corpse quietly lying on it. This should be the punishment for someone from the 21st floor who broke the rules. I couldn't help but feel scared, because if I had eaten the chicken wing yesterday, I would have received the same punishment today. Before I could react, I saw Laura from upstairs frantically kicking the food down. But she was still one step too late, because she had secretly kept food. This caused the temperature on her floor to rise sharply and she was burned alive and dropped down. Jenny tried to use a bed sheet to extinguish the fire, but it was too late. In an instant, Laura was burned to a charred corpse. By the time I reacted, platform started moving down to the next floor. Tony told us to quickly clear the food, and the room returned to its normal temperature. Because of the thief's disregard for the rules, today's food could not be eaten in the fight, so the people below had no food to eat. From the third day on, I began to follow the rules. I only ate my own pizza every day. To enforce the rules strictly, Tony threw away all the food from the people who died yesterday. But on this day, After eating pizza for more than 20 days straight, I suddenly had an idea. I pretended to throw away the food and secretly grabbed a piece of food and stuffed it in my mouth. But this scene was noticed by the people above. However, they didn't expose me. Soon, it was time to change floors. Good news came from downstairs that food could be delivered intact to the one hundred and seventy fifth floor. Jenny and I happily started dancing, but when we woke up the next day, we found we had been assigned to the one hundred and eightieth floor, the floor where food had never reached.

The wife gently brushed back the woman's hair, and the husband beside her felt a pang of jealousy. The mischievous woman shook her hair again, causing the wife to burst into uncontrollable laughter. Husband quickly found an excuse to send the woman away. The woman's name was Jenny, and she had turned her own story into a novel. As soon as it was published, it caused a sensation throughout Paris. Though Jenny was the author, she willingly gave the credit to her husband, will. Now everyone knew will is the author of the novel, with no idea that it was actually Jenny who had written it. Every time Jenny went out, her husband worried that she might reveal the truth. To protect his reputation, will bought a house in the countryside, claiming it was a gift for Jenny, but really wanting to keep her away from the city to avoid exposing the secret of. Of course, Jenny had no idea about her husband's ulterior motive and gratefully thanked will. She settled happily into the country house. However, Jenny spent most of her time gardening and and the progress on her novel slowed significantly. This made will very dissatisfied. With no other choice, Jenny had to focus on her writing again. Soon the sequel was released and sold extremely well. One day, Jenny's husband took her out for a trip, but then a noble woman recognized will as the famous author and took the opportunity to get to know the couple. At a dinner party, Jenny showed great interest in the noble woman, who was equally intrigued by her. The noble woman even invited Jenny to her home for a small gathering right in front of Jenny's husband. After the noble woman left, Jenny quickly asked her husband if he would mind. To her surprise, he was very supportive. That day, Jenny knocked on the noble woman's door. When Jenny returned home in the evening, her husband called her over because he was very interested in what had happened. But how could Jenny tell him? Out of curiosity, will found an opportunity to go to the noble woman's house. Although he didn't say anything, the noble woman immediately understood his purpose and let him in without hesitation. Jenny was completely unaware of all this. While she was at the noble woman's house, her husband was at home, and when she returned, he quietly went to the noble woman's house again. However, over time, Jenny began to sense something was amiss. She took advantage of her husband's absent and quietly went to the noble woman's house. Sure enough, she saw a figure that looked very much like her husband.

Would you marry an old man who's 300 years older than you? The old man used his eight meter long fingernails to slash open his own blood vessel. He wanted to exchange blood with Ivy. All the vampires salivated greedily. It was the noble blood of their vampire king. Ivy endured her disgust and took a bite. Immediately, changes began to happen to her body. The blood vessels on her face bulged outward, her nails turned black, and long and sharp fangs grew in her mouth. Ivy successfully transformed into a vampire and gained powerful strength. She smiled faintly and set her plan in motion. She walked up to the vampire king, who was still thinking about drinking her blood to attain immortality together. But just as he reached out to pull her, Ivy suddenly ran to the table and knocked over the candle. The fire spread instantly. She seized the opportunity to grab an ancient Ebony wood and stabbed it fiercely into the vampire king's heart. The vampire king was instantly severely weakened, his appearance gradually aging into a rapid old man. Ivy took the chance to escape, but was caught by the vampire king's mother. Enraged, she lifted Ivy up when suddenly a blond woman appeared behind her. Turned out that after Ivy drank the vampire king's blood, all the vampires were eager to drain her blood dry, as it would enhance their own cultivation. The blond woman and the vampire king's mother fought fiercely, evenly matched. Ivy Slipped away quietly. Unexpectedly, the vampire king suddenly appeared and grabbed her by the neck. As Ivy was choked and unable to breathe, she secretly took out a steel wire and sliced off the vampire king's arm in one swift move. She then kicked him into the blazing fire, and the vampire king turned to ashes. Instantly, Ivy transformed back into a normal human. Afterwards, she set the entire manor on fire and left triumphantly.

Victor opened fire inside the police station, but the officers didn't fall. Instantly he tried to reach the door to trigger the alarm, failed. Just then, two officers returned to the station, and Victor calmly disguised himself as a delivery man, telling them that someone had accidentally fallen and gotten hurt. As they went to investigate, Victor raised his pistol and shot both officers before they could even react. Another officer heard the gunfire and rushed out from his office, and Victor once again disguised himself as a delivery man, claiming he was just delivering balloons. Using the balloons as cover, he pulled the trigger again, knocking the officer down. And even mock are all the officers in this station idiots? At that moment, a vigilant female officer, Emily, drew her gun and stepped out. Victor swiftly pulled out an assault rifle, forcing her to retreat. Emily dashed to the safest spot, hiding behind bulletproof glass, began entering the code to open the steel door. Bullets pelted the glass like a relentless hailstorm as Victor fired shot after shot. Finally, the glass shattered. Just as he was about to fire again, his ammunition ran out. Seeing this, Emily immediately returned fire, simultaneously pushing open the cell door and ducking inside. Bullets rattled down once more, but when she looked down, she realized she had been hit. It turned out the girl had found her mother's photo stuck on a Tombstone.

Lila tore the photo from the frame, grabbed the relics and prepared to bring them back for her mother. However, as soon as she left, a billionaire arrived at the cemetery to mourn his wife who had been dead for six years. When he realized the photo and relics were missing, he flew into a rage. His assistant quickly pulled up the cemetery surveillance footage and once they identified the target, they jumped into the car and chased after Lila. In less than 10 seconds, they caught up with her. The billionaire, Mister Grant, stepped out of the car, demanding she returned the Jade pendant, precious relic of his late wife. Lila refused, even demanding a one million dollar Ransom. She needed the money to pay for her mother's treatment and threatened to smash the pendant if he didn't comply. Mister Grant was helpless, angrily throwing a stack of cash on the ground, giving in to Lila. But this was just the beginning of her nightmare. As the billionaire drove away, at that very moment, Lila's mother was being wheeled out by Doctor Harper. Mister Grant unknowingly passed by his wife, separated from her for six long years. Lila immediately picked up the money from the ground, handing it to the doctor, pleading for her mother to be operated on. But Doctor Harper refused because Lila had offended a very powerful person. Helpless, Lila had no choice but to take her mother to another hospital. But no matter how desperately She begged. Not a single hospital would treat her, until the day she met a kind female DOC who told her that only with a letter of forgiveness, personally signed by that powerful individual, would any hospital dare to save her mother. Hearing this?

Who could have imagined that a tiny monkey would change the life of a paralyzed boy named Leo? A few days earlier, he had jumped into the river to bathe, but bacteria in the water entered his bloodstream, causing swelling in his brain and paralyzing his entire body. Now he sat in a wheelchair, feeling like a burden. Sometimes when he watched the fish swimming in the lake, he felt the urge to jump back in and end everything. But his father, Ethan, stopped him just in time. Seeing all this, his mother, Sophia, was completely devastated and immediately sought medical help to get him better as quickly as possible. Afterward, he was taken to a center where trained animals are adopted to assist people. Liam held hope that he might also find a companion. There. His eyes landed on a small monkey with dark fur who had once worked in a circus. Seeing it brought a faint smile to Liam's face. But the monkey was quite mischievous, sometimes teasing him, sometimes calling him closer. The doctor explained that the monkey had helped several paralyzed individuals before. Soon as Liam approached, the monkey suddenly became calm. Seeing Liam in a wheelchair, it looked sad. Soon, Liam brought the monkey home. The monkey spent all day in its cage watching Liam as if it understood his condition. Liam was happy. He finally had someone who truly saw him and felt him. One day, something unusual happened while his father, Ethan, was Helping him exercise, the monkey slipped out of its cage. It approached with a ball in its hands and hugged Liam, as if saying, I'm here for you. This made Liam smile. From that moment on, the monkey began to actively help him.

As soon as Max stepped onto the bus, in less than a second, the entire bus was drenched in his sweat. Seeing the bus fill up like that, the driver had no choice but to blacklist him, never letting him ride again. With no other option, Max decided to take a taxi. But when the driver saw him, he immediately cranked the air conditioner to full blast, barely averting a disaster. When he got home, Max wanted to roast a fish to relax. But the moment he approached the stove, sweat gushed out, instantly putting out the fire and even reviving the fish. He had no choice but to order takeout. When the delivery guy arrived at the door, he froze in fear seeing a dozen fans running in the house simultaneously. Because the moment Max stepped away from the fans, sweat would pour out non stop. The delivery guy was completely dumbfounded on the spot. Even worse was the office cleaner. Just after mopping the floor, Max walked in, leaving a trail of water everywhere, completely unaware of the chaos he was causing. One day after Max fixed a client's computer, a colleague walked in and Max became unbearably hot. Sweat spurted out, instantly destroying the client's computer completely. The client had no choice but to get a brand new machine.

Henry accidentally dropped a duck egg and it shattered on the floor. Then a metallic sound echoed from the broken shell. He lifted the pieces and was stunned to find solid gold inside. He rushed to get it tested and soon confirmed it was pure gold. Henry hurried home to tell his wife Clara, but she suddenly broke down in tears. Only then did he realize she had sold the Drake to a local farmer, George. Panicking, Henry raced to the farm and offered triple the price to buy it back. George allowed them to search the yard themselves, but every duck looked exactly the same and they failed to identify the right one. Then Henry remembered the Drake reacted to bark. The whole family crouched, tried imitating a dog, but still nothing happened. Young Leo walked off disappointed. Quietly, a duck followed him. It turned out to be the one he had raided. The family quickly surrounded it and Henry barked again. The Drake instantly laid an egg. They cracked it open and found another gold egg inside. They hid all the eggs separately and began treating the duck like a priceless treasure. Later, Clara received a call from a creditor and stole an egg to head to the bank. When she couldn't cash it, she was thrown out. She then went to a refinery and exchanged it for a pile of money, clearing her debts and even buying new clothes. Henry noticed and demanded the truth, and Clara Confessed everything, they erupted into a fierce argument. Later, a friend named Ethan heard the story and encouraged Clara to keep selling the eggs, insisting no one would believe a duck could lay gold.

When the host, Mister Carter, announced his name, everyone was certain he would lose. This was his very first robot fight, and he had built his robot, blaze, in just one month. On the other hand, the opponent's robot was much larger and more powerful, equipped with A I. Technology, making it even more dangerous. In all previous matches, it had never been defeated. The game began and both robots entered the arena. The opponent's robot bared its sharp teeth as if it would swallow Blaze's hole. The whistle blew and the fight started. The two robots collided fiercely, but Ethan barely managed to keep blaze's intact. Knew that a direct collision was impossible to win, so he carefully tried to anticipate the opponent's moves. The opposing robot had cameras on both sides, instantly detecting any side attack, allowing it to counter quickly. Ethan cleverly dodged and tried to strike from the side, but this time he was caught. Blaze's front was badly damaged. The host discussed the next move when the opposing robot suddenly launched another attack on blaze. Blaze was forced to retreat. However, he ended up trapped in a part of the field where a trap had already been set. Ethan tried to escape, but the opponent's Robot was ready. Its AI system had already tracked every move of blaze. The giant robot attacked relentlessly, smashing blaze apart.

Two boys were pulling their bicycles out of the river when a small nuclear bomb accidentally stuck to their magnet. As soon as the police received the news, they immediately sealed off the entire area because an international competition was about to take place there. When some divers went into the water to inspect the spot, they suddenly saw the body of a humpback whale, half of it missing. At the same time, a dark shadow passed right behind them, frightening them. They told the team above to pull the rope quickly. After surfacing, they reported everything to Lisa, but she didn't take their warning seriously at all. Lisa herself went deep underwater with her team to catch the shark. Right in front of her was a huge pile of human skulls. Above the skulls, many baby sharks were swimming. Once the game began, they could attack people. But Mayor Collins ignored the danger and started the competition anyway. At that moment, Lisa used explosives to kill the baby sharks. The babies were gone, but the blast woke up their mother. She rose to the surface and flipped Lisa's boat, but she didn't attack Lisa. Seeking revenge for her babies, she charged straight toward the competition like a raging creature. As players began to sink one by one, people realized something was terribly wrong. Suddenly, a girl screamed that there was a shark in the water. Before everyone could escape, the shark killed one of the players. The mayor finally. Realized he had made a massive mistake, but it was too late to fix anything. The police kept firing at the shark, so the shark intentionally swam toward an area filled with old World War 2 cannon shells. And after a while, a massive explosion occurred.

This boy named Ethan had endured bullying for years. So he joined a local fight club and started pounding the heavy bag. A wrestler named Mason was surprised by his fierce determination. But that session didn't last long. The head coach spotted him and shouted at him furiously because it broke the club's training rules. Later, Mason told Ethan to follow him. And because of the boy's passion, Mason began to train him personally. From that day, Ethan's true boxing journey officially began. Mason took him under his wing and taught him every technique. Ethan then trained relentlessly, day and forgetting meals and sleep, completely absorbed in combat practice. Slowly, he mastered the hidden skills of fighting as well. Under Mason's harsh training, Ethan was transformed entirely. The timid kid had become bold and powerful like a raging lion. After six months of nonstop practice, Ethan finally turned into a rail fighter. Now it was time to settle old scores. He returned to the same alley where those punks once made him cry. But this time, he didn't come to shed tears, came to make others tremble. And from there, his payback truly began. One day, by chance, he ran into a former thug inside a supermarket. This time, he was no helpless victim. He beat the guy brutally in front of everyone. Especially in front of the new girl, so that the thug would taste the humiliation Ethan once suffered. But his real target was the gang leader Vince As the furious Ethan walked toward him, Vince desperately searched for something to use. But the tables had dramatically turned. Ethan wrapped a bottle in his shirt and lashed it like a whip. Vince writhed in agony, immediately surrendered and handed over the money he had kept from him for two full years.

Grayson had to arrange 12 keys perfectly, with not a single one allowed to be out of place. But when his friend took just one of them away, his smile froze instantly, as if time itself had stopped. He found an excuse and quickly ran to the restroom, pulled an antibacterial soap from his pocket, aligned the little box neatly, and scrubbed his hands with great force and attention. He washed for a full half hour until his fingers began bleeding from the friction, used up every single tissue just to wipe the blood away. Then he noticed a stain had appeared on his clothes, and he began scrubbing it frantically with all his strength. After another full 30 minutes, he finally completed a thorough cleaning and prepared to leave. He saw the doorknob was far too dirty to touch, but all the paper towels nearby had been completely used up. He had no choice but to stand helplessly by the door for an entire hour. He slipped out quickly the moment someone pushed it open. Grayson had built the most advanced and precise airplane in the world, yet he was still not satisfied with the rivets on its body. He instructed the engineers to remove every single rivet to minimize air resistance as much as possible. A few months later, the plane's surface became so smooth it resembled a flawless mirror. After meticulously checking every tiny detail, Grayson finally smiled, feeling fully satisfied.

Dante was examining the mummy without wearing gloves. The next second, the mummy's sharp teeth sliced into his finger. Blood started dripping rapidly. Panic, he rushed toward the first aid kit. He had no idea that his blood had already fallen onto the mummy's body. And the moment it touched her, something inside her began to subtly change. He he managed to wrap a bandage around his finger, then prepared to separate the mummy from the stone slab. But when he tried, he realized the mummy was completely stuck to it. With no other option, he grabbed a metal rod and carefully pried her loose. After several tense moments, he finally succeeded. Then, with extreme caution, he lifted the mummy and placed her on a small bed nearby. He turned back to clean the dirt and debris stuck to the slab. As he focused on his work, the mummy's jaw suddenly twitched. Sight froze him in sheer shock. Quickly, he pulled a sheet and completely covered the mummy. Trying to ignore what he had just witnessed, he returned to his work. But then something even more unsettling occurred. The mummy moved again, slowly, yet he still didn't notice. Moments later, his boss, Mister Whitman, arrived to inspect the progress. By then, Dante had discovered a hidden compartment inside the slab. He removed the cover and found a small keyhole like opening. Mister Whitman wanted to open it immediately, but Dante refused, warning it could be a trap. Carefully, he used Pliers to insert a metal piece into the opening. When he pressed it, the secret chamber unlocked. Inside was a golden skeletal staff. The sight left everyone holding their breath just before Dante was about to eat his steak.

Veronica staged an accident to get a free lunch, deliberately knocking over the ketchup she just squeezed, then pretending to slip. This trick could earn her compensation from the restaurant. Veronica was a professional scammer. Her trunk was full of tools of the trade. One day she noticed a man buying a massive flat screen TV. She focused on the TV size, knowing it would block the rearview mirror. She had to watch traffic from the side mirror, standing in the driver's blind spot. Sure enough, after a scream, the man saw Veronica lying there, wanted to check on her. But seeing the expensive car, Veronica instantly acted dramatically. Clutching her head, she secured a hefty payout. This made Veronica feel prouder, but it didn't stop her. She quickly regroup, ready to hunt the next target. Soon her eyes landed on an elderly lady collecting loose change. Missus Collins rest elegantly. Veronica knew a big score was coming when Missus Collins got into the car to start it. Veronica readied herself, but she was unexpectedly struck by another speeding vehicle. Missus Collins in the car didn't notice, still began to reverse. The car bounced over Veronica. Missus Collins quickly called emergency services. Firefighters arrived fast. Grabbed by Missus Collins as she explained the situation. Veronica was an old acquaintance, a professional at staged accidents, but this time she had been really hurt. Firefighters kept reassuring her it was a minor injury, quickly treated. Soon Veronica was pulled from under the Car next. She was rushed to the hospital for full medical treatment. At this point, Veronica still didn't recognize her mistake, kept demanding double compensation. Firefighters could only warn her this behavior was extremely dangerous.

The man shoved handfuls of ice into his mouth in a panic. And suddenly, Noah's eyes filled with tears. He scraped the mold off an old crack, spread the very last bit of caviar on it, and forced himself to swallow every crumb. It was the only food Noah had left. He'd been trapped inside this mansion for three long days. He originally came here to steal a priceless painting. When he tried to leave, he entered the wrong access code. The security system locked down and cut Noah off from his partners. He noticed the door looked like ordinary wood, so he pulled out his knife and started carving at it like a madman. But when he finally opened a tiny hole, he discovered heavy steel plating on the other side. Feeling completely desperate, Noah went to the kitchen for water, but not a single drop came from the tap. He crawled into the indoor greenhouse, trying to activate the sprinkler system, but nothing happened at all. Inside the fridge, he found only expired caviar and moldy crackers. The following day, Noah realized even the fruit on the table wasn't real. Each piece had been carved from stone. He grabbed one and hurled it at the window. Surprisingly, the stone fruit shattered on impact, but the glass didn't even scratch. That's when Noah finally understood. This entire house was designed as an anti burglar trap. Suddenly, the air conditioning switched to heating, raising the temperature. He headed to the Pool hoping to cool off, only to discover it was filled with salt water. Even the fish tank was packed with seawater. Just when Noah thought he couldn't sink any lower, he spotted a maid on the security camera feed. He grabbed a frying pan in excitement and banged wildly against the door. But the soundproof walls swallowed everything.

France's most hilarious performer is once again back in action, this time turning himself into a truly justice driven special agent, colliding head on with a master thief who just stole a priceless rare jewel. Not long ago, Adrian swiped a gemstone worth an almost insane fortune, and the moment he crawled out of the filthy sewer, a dog started barking endlessly without stopping. Its noise immediately alerted Officer Cole nearby. Cole dropped down from above with surprising and agile speed, and neither man wasted a single unnecessary word. They launched straight into an intense brawl. Their fight climbed from the very first floor all the way to the eighth, and elderly lady in the restroom at that moment had to squeeze everything shut in complete shock. Cole told her calmly to stay absolutely calm, then grabbed her oxygen tank and forcefully hurled it at Adrian. After all that unbelievable chaos, both men were somehow totally fine and unharmed. France's population theoretically minus 2. Just joking, obviously. Cole grabbed a pair of Scissors and jabbed like he was doing delicate embroidery work. Adrian snatched an electric clipper and angrily threw it right back. Adrian remained completely untouched. Cole lost a small noticeable chunk of hair. They were so focused on beating each other senseless that the precious stone slipped all the way to the ground below. They immediately stopped and rushed straight after it. Cole was about to chase the barking dog right away when Adrian knocked him out with A heavy and solid blow

On his first day as a monk, Leo secretly roasted some meat for dinner. That night, he took all the steamed buns. Master Lee asked how he could eat so many.
