Leo said that eating these buns would give him strength for training. Master Lee hadn't eaten meat in over 10 years. He immediately laughed and told Leo to share the buns with everyone. The next day during training, Leo discovered a small bird's nest. Unexpectedly, the abbot walked by. He quickly looked for a place to hide the birds. But Master Lee saw the whole scene. Master Lee accused them of taking lives. Leo said he was saving lives. This made Master Lee very angry. He said he clearly saw them catching birds to eat. Leo took out the bird's nest. Master Lee picked up each bird to check. Surprisingly, every bird was still alive. Leo immediately took out the worms in his hand. He said he wanted to feed the birds, was saving lives. But masterly said it was also killing. Worms have lives too. You can't use them to feed the birds. A junior, brother Ming said, if the birds don't eat, the worms will starve. That's also killing. Leo suddenly didn't know what to do. At that moment, the bell from martial arts practice rang. He handed Both the worms and the birds to Master Lee. Then he ran away quickly. Master Lee looked at the birds and worms in his hand, feeling extremely conflict. What do you think? Should we save the worms or the birds first

Some people tied heavy stones to an unsuspecting donkey and threw it forcefully into the river, sending water splashing everywhere. Within a moment, the donkey sank deep beneath the surface. A swarm of small fish quickly gathered, voraciously feeding, and the donkey ultimately perished. The onlookers stood on the Riverbank watching this shocking scene unfold with cold detachment. Suddenly, they were startled to see a young boy struggling fiercely in the water. They shouted desperately trying to get him to come out. But Lucas completely ignored their calls. He pushed forward with determination, swimming swiftly and without hesitation. At that critical moment, a massive fish suddenly surged from beneath the water, swallowing Lucas hole in a single terrifying gull. He found himself trapped deep inside the fish's enormous belly. Inside felt like a vast, mysterious and shadowy cavern stretching endlessly. Panic, Lucas began shouting for help with all his strength. Suddenly, a strange fish appeared right before him. It had a shocking human like face. The fish conveyed its past to Luke, revealing that it had once been human, but was trapped inside the fish for many years due to an ancient curse. Hearing this, a dazzling, brilliant light suddenly appeared ahead. Lucas moved carefully but determinedly toward the glow and he saw a man standing within. It was none other than his long lost father, Marcus. Overwhelmed by shock and joy, Lucas ran straight into his father's arms, holding him tightly. Tears and emotions blending in this extraordinary moment.

The moment Logan stepped onto the stone tiles, the walls on either side of the fire pit began to close in. The only way out right now was the blazing coal path ahead. He grabbed a painting and hurled it at the opposite wall, then carefully laid rolled up paper along the coal path before it could catch fire. Logan sprinted onto the paper, running like a man possessed. But what he didn't expect was as soon as he burst through the iron gate, two spiked bamboo panels swung violently toward him. He scrambled back to the gate, pressing hard to keep it shut. It turned out the bamboo spikes were controlled by the iron gate itself. If the gate dropped, Logan would be skewered flat like a pancake. He ripped down the painting, snatched the stick hidden inside and used it to prop the iron gate open. Finally, he was safe. Breathing heavily, Logan pointed at the bamboo spikes that almost killed him, wagging his finger in frustration. Seeing the token right in front of him, he reached for it, only to be pushed back by a row of falling spikes. The stone beast guarding the token lunged at it. Luckily, Logan had lightning fast reflexes. The stone beast closed in rapidly. With no other option, he began running circles around the incense burner and the beast couldn't catch him at all. Infuriated, the beast's ears suddenly extended, yanking him into the air and kicking him hard while Logan Was still recovering.

Eva burned herself with a curling iron when suddenly the kettle beside her started shaking. She lifted the lid and a stack of cash shot out. She burned herself again, and the kettle spat out even more money. She couldn't believe it, so she turned and kicked the table hard. The next second, the kettle threw out another 400 bucks. Her boyfriend Ryan came home and saw the mess, thinking someone had broken in. But Eva simply handed him the kettle, then slapped him across the face. Just as Ryan was about to lose it, the kettle dropped another stack of bills. He finally realized the more pain they endured, the more money the kettle produced. They tested it again and again, discovering the worst the pain, the bigger the payout. So they decided to make a million. They held their hands over the stove, screaming in agony as the kettle sprayed cash like crazy. Eva went to a beauty salon to rip out her leg hair. Orion had a tooth pulled without anesthesia. Their screams, combined with the fountain of money, soon earned them 200 grand. They stuffed the cash into the toilet tank and went on a shopping spree, their lives completely transformed. To uncover the kettle's origins, they joined an appraisal show and visited the library. They Learned it was 2,000 years old and every past owner had met a tragic end. That night, an eastern man, Mister Leong, found them at a party, warning them to Throw the kettle away. They ignored him. Late that night, burglars broke into their home, taking all the money, claiming the kettle belonged to their family. But they didn't want the kettle, only the cash it produced.

In the post apocalyptic subway station, the only way to survive was to stay on the green tiles. Step off, and the monsters would strike without mercy. When hundreds of survivors realized there were only 52 safe zone, the scramble turned instantly into a fight for life and death. The station echoed with screams. Only the territory controlled by the gang remained untouched. Anyone who dared enter would instantly become a target, riddled by bullets from their weapons. As monsters poured in, they tore through humans without hesitation, screams following one after another. Only those standing on the green tiles were protected. Within minutes, less than half of the survivors were left. Then the Game Master appeared once more to ramp up the stakes. He announced that the next round would have just one safe zone. Only one person could survive. Just as despair set in, a green tile appeared beneath the gang leader rider's feet. At that moment, a man named Cole offered a fortune to claim the safe zone. But after securing it, he personally destroyed the last refuge. Everyone was stunned, scrambling to stop him. But it was too late. The safe zone was obliterated. Now no one had a safe place. And that was exactly what Cole wanted. Only by erasing every escape route would humans stop fighting one another and finally unite against the monsters.

The road was empty, and a truck crawled along at a painfully slow pace. Eager to get home, Sophie sped up to pass it, but the truck suddenly surged forward, cutting back in front of her. Sophie steadied her car and drove cautiously. Every time she slowed down, the truck mirrored her speed, blocking her path again and again. Not wanting trouble, she accelerated to overtake, and the truck responded immediately, sticking close behind. This time it was so near it nearly clipped her bumper. Confused and frustrated, she pushed her pedal further, reaching 75 miles per hour, but the truck refused to back off. The two vehicles were now side by side on the highway, a dangerous dance that could end in disaster. Sophie slammed on the brakes and fell back behind the truck. After several rounds of this deadly game, she realized the driver was reckless and decided to keep a safe distance behind the truck. Then, unexpectedly, the truck driver gestured for her to pass. Sophie hesitated, thinking of her mother waiting at home. She had no choice but to accelerate and overtake, but the truck surged forward again, blocking her path. As she stared in disbelief, a car came from the opposite lane. Panic struck. She slammed the brakes and narrowly avoided a collision. Shaken to her core, Sophie pulled over to rest, planning to continue once the truck was gone. She sat in her car for half an hour before finally getting back on the Road

Monsters wandered slowly through the streets, but no one on the sidewalks could actually see their presence at all. Even when someone was suddenly swallowed and screamed, no one stopped. Because in the future world, the moment people opened their eyes, their bodies would instantly be encased in a transparent bubble. The bubble carried them across the entire busy city. Inside it, they watched videos, browsed all sorts of gossip, news, track their friends movements and locations in real time. Even while brushing their teeth or using the restroom, the virtual assistant constantly guided their every single action. No one looked at the real world anymore. No one realized that monsters were quietly standing right beside. Until one day on her way to work, Lila suddenly saw the entire street filled completely with terrifying monsters. What terrified her even more was that she realized she was the only person who could actually see them. She immediately hid in a corner, desperately trying to tell the truth to her friend. But the moment she opened her mouth, she watched a monster mercilessly swallow her best friend. Lila almost completely broke down and Doctor Kane told her that there was a hidden passage that could lead her safely out of the city. But after she turned off her bubble, she realized she didn't know the streets at all. Monsters were everywhere. She didn't dare take even a single wrong step. She frantically tried to run through the streets to escape, Was nearly torn apart by the monsters at the most dangerous moment.

Clara never touched the food they brought to her. Instead, she smeared it all over the wall, using the salt from the soup to slowly corrode the surface. She dug into the wall with a homemade iron spoon, scattering the dirt outside the window carefully. She was trapped in a prison completely surrounded by water. To prevent the guards from discovering her hole, she tore pages from books and soaked them in water, then covered them with dirt so that the paper would perfectly match the walls color. She used the paper to cleverly conceal the hole. After three months, she had dug a tunnel over 500 meters long. On this particular day, the prosecutor came to inspect the prison and Clara knew this was her chance to escape. Since she hadn't left her cell in so long, not even her cellmates had seen her. The guards didn't notice her presence at all. So she quietly walked right back into her cell. Guard Mills arrived to deliver her meal. As usual, he knocked, but there was no response whatsoever. He quickly unlocked the door, only to find the cell completely empty. He rushed to alert Warden Harris. When the warden arrived, he angrily scolded the guard in charge. Furious, he grabbed a book and threw it at the wall, then tore down a newspaper and discovered the tunnel. He immediately ordered his men to take action.

Before digging any grave, Ethan always took a small pinch of soil, placed it in his mouth and chewed it, using the taste to judge whether the ground was fit for digging. But this time, the moment the dirt touched his tongue, knew something was terribly wrong. Even though the job paid a fortune, Ethan couldn't walk away just on a hunch. He ordered the workers to unearth the coffin. The moment the earth was disturbed, they found something strange, something downright terrifying. The coffin on top was immaculate, flawlessly clean. Yet from beneath the soil came eerie creaking noises. Ethan panicked and clawed at the dirt with his bare hands. Sure enough, another coffin emerged beneath the first. His chest tightened. He had seen double burials before, but never one coffin buried directly under another. He immediately called his team and when half the soil was cleared, they discovered the lower coffin was wrapped in thick iron wires. No one could tell if the wires were meant to keep people out or to keep something in. To make matters worse, the coffin was nearly 10 feet long, completely unnatural in size. The coffin alone was eerie enough and night was falling fast. Victor suggested they move it down the mountain first, store it safely in the temple warehouse, prevent any unforeseen trouble. For Protection, they covered the coffin with sticky rice, splashed pigs blood over it and sealed it with protective charms. Just then, a woman arrived. Her face Pale with shock. How could there be another coffin buried beneath my father's grave? When Ethan asked, she revealed an old photograph.

But afterward, tears welled up in Oliver's eyes. He felt immense remorse for killing the innocent creature. His thinking was like that of a three year old. His mother didn't pay much attention to him and the doctor had said that Oliver probably wouldn't live past 10 years old. He was fortunate to have a brother, Ethan, who loved him very much, taking care of him every day and being extremely attentive. One day while Ethan was working, he left Oliver alone in the shop. But Oliver quietly slipped out of the shop and climbed a tall tower. A crowd gathered below to watch him. The police tried to coax him down with a loud speaker, but Oliver climbed even higher. Then Ethan started singing Oliver's favorite song for the Louds. As soon as Oliver heard the song, he immediately began to climb down. The next morning when he woke up and washed his face, remembered that Oliver might still be in the bathtub. He rushed there and found Oliver still In the tub, shivering from the cold. Every time a prisoner needed to use the restroom, the officers would meticulously inspect the toilet. Even with such care, accidents still happen. Nina cut the ropes, binding her hands with the knife, then used the sound of flushing as cover to load the gun. She didn't rush out immediately, instead hiding the gun in her waistband, retied the cut ropes, and calmly walked out of the bathroom. The two female officers, Tina and Monica, noticed nothing unusual, unaware that a tragedy was about to unfold. Later, Tina and Monica escorted Nina to the airport terminal. Seeing this, her accomplices moved in to rescue her. Several male officers were going through security. A man, Rico, threw a smoke grenade on the ground. His job was to help a different woman fall asleep every night, but he wasn't selling his body at all. What he truly offered was comfort and calm. As the company's top ranked sleep companion, Nilo had to obey three unbreakable rules, no unbuttoning a client's clothes, no reacting to flirtatious talk and absolutely no dozing off himself. With touch free soothing and aromatherapy, most clients drifted off within minutes. But tonight he received an unusual request. Taylor booked a full four hour session in one go. Nilo showered, changed into pajamas and settled into the bed as usual. But Taylor suddenly seemed anxious. Sticking to the routine, Nilo guided her to lie on her side. Yet Taylor's body kept sliding closer. He sensed it instantly, gently pushing her away and stacking two pillows to keep distance. Taylor exploded. How could a sleep companion act so aloof? She stormed into the living room demanding a refund. Reluctantly, Nilo started calculating the charges. Sandwiches, essential oils, drinks, toiletries, plus service fees. In the end, he could only give her back $500. Taylor grew even more frustrated. Since the money was spent, she might as well finish the night. Back in bed, Nilo resumed the aromatherapy and fitted her eye mask. But Taylor couldn't stay quiet for even three seconds before speaking up again. Act normal. I can't fall asleep like this. Nero's face tightened. He wanted to talk over fast, but Taylor kept going. Can you take the glove off? Feels Weird. Nero reluctantly complied. No one expected what happened next. The company's star sleep coach actually fell asleep at her place, a direct violation of all three rules. Nilo apologized non stop, begging Taylor not to leave a bad review. He rushed back to the office to confess only for his boss to praise him instead. Taylor had not only left five stars, but booked him for the entire month. Over the next weeks, Nilo accompanied her night after night. He Learned Taylor had just ended a ten year relationship and the pain hit him, too. Even when serving other clients, his mind drifted to Taylor's social posts. He had fallen for someone he shouldn't. Tonight was the final session. Taylor cooked him an elaborate dinner and they talked about everything from the news to late night shows until the mood subtly shifted. They leaned closer and closer when suddenly Nelo's phone rang.

Every time she dipped her hand into the crystal clear ocean, thousands of fish swarmed around her. The fisherman weren't surprised anymore when never she joined them on their boats. They never returned empty handed. Her gift fed the entire island. But that wasn't the only miracle. Every morning a long line formed outside her house. People whispered that a single touch from her could heal anything. Cuts vanished in an instant. Aches faded away. Soon the villagers treated her like a living goddess. Then one day everything changed. She went to the mountains with her friends where they discovered a massive beehive. As she approached, the furious buzzing stopped. The bees landed softly on her palm, bowing as if she were their queen. Thrilled, she turned to show her friends only to see horror unfold. The bees had attacked. One of them panicked. She clenched her fist and in that single motion, every bee dropped dead. Frozen with fear, she realised what had happened. She thought everyone would now see her as a monster. She made her friends swear never to tell a soul. From that day on, her powers began to fade. Her touch could no longer heal. The fisherman caught fewer fish and the villagers were left bewildered, unable to understand what had happened to their miracle girl.

voice_to_text: The entire institute is plunged into shock and grief, grief because a longtime friend was on that vessel, shock because a massive research ship shouldn't go down for no reason. Not until they watch the rescue footage where the sunken vessel is encircled by a glowing white ring and sharp, piercing noises echo all around it. Even the veteran professor who spent decades studying the sea has never seen anything like this, let alone the intern, Kelly. Yet unexpectedly, Kelly is the one who uncovers the cause of the accident. Back at the coastal station, she finds a video message left by her friend before the disaster, but she missed it because she was out drinking that night. The guilt of losing her last chance to speak to her best friend crushes her. But soon she notices something unusual in the video. Right before the recording ends, a white light rises outside the window, the same glow as the deep sea light paired with the same shrill noise. To test her theory, Kelly extracts both audio samples, the one from the message and the one from the deep. The comparison shows they match almost perfectly. Kelly concludes the shipwreck is tied to these strange signals. She immediately reports her findings to the old professor, but this is far beyond what the professor can accept. She refuses to believe anything supernatural exists in the ocean. Their argument escalates and they part on bad terms. However, Professor Seagle overhears and makes a New discovery. When he gets home, he receives whale footage sent by kit comparing the two. The same white light and bizarre noise appear again. Tests confirm the match. The professor realizes she wrongfully blamed Kelly. Too proud to apologize herself, she asks Seagull to deliver the footage to Kelly on his way to a global ocean conference. Seagull acknowledges Kelly's findings. The tension between Kelly and the professor finally eases. They are getting closer to the truth. But as Kelly walks Seagull to the helicopter, a catastrophe of unprecedented scale erupts. Because the bearded researcher running experiments notices everyone's phones suddenly start ringing. He checks his own and sees a tsunami emergency alert. Kelly City is listed among the three danger zones. He calls her immediately, but Kelly didn't bring her phone while seeing Seagull off. Luckily, just before take off, Seagull receives the institute's emergency warning. He drags Kelly away from the danger zone. Minutes later, the tsunami slams into the coast. Watching her entire station wiped out so effortlessly leaves Kelly trembling. At least she is alive. Others aren't so fortunate. Blocks of seabirds suddenly flee inland in panic and the shoreline retreats dramatically. Anyone who has lived through a tsunami knows this is the omen of a coming catastrophe. People sprint wildly. Drivers slam the gas. Those on foot wish they could grow wings, but nothing can outrun the fury of the sea. Three coastal nations are struck simultaneously. The Global Ocean Organization immediately takes action. During the emergency summit, a virologist speech shocks every top scientist present, and they realize a threat far more terrifying than the tsunami is rapidly approaching.

As the first country to make contact, the UK carried the heavy burden of hosting the initial peace talk. The government had to spend a fortune to build an auditorium for the negotiation. The time for the talks quickly arrived, and at the agreed upon noon hour, Kate ordered the floodgates to be open and the aquatics entered the auditorium through pipes. As the water chamber began to fill with sea water, it was finally time for the envoys arrival. The first four aquatics to enter were clearly guarded, followed by two creatures that resembled catfish, who likely served as the envoys assistants or think tank. The most surprising arrival, however, was the envoy himself, whose appearance was clearly more in line with human aesthetics. Everyone was momentarily stunned, but Kate quickly motioned for a delegate to step forward and speak, and humanity's representative was Sir Jonathan. We don't need translation. The envoy had already taught himself human languages. Jonathan quickly got to the point, presenting a gift on behalf of his people to make amends for the friction between the two sides.

A young woman ordered a luxury meal, but the moment she lifted the lid, her heart nearly stopped. The box was completely empty and even the receipt was blank. Furious, she tried calling the restaurant, only to find the number didn't connect at all. Confused and uneasy, she noticed a strange note inside. Write down any food you want and place it in the box. Thinking it had to be a joke, she played along, scribbled barbecue on a slip of paper and tossed it inside. Seconds later, the box rattled violently and burst with a flash of white light. When it stopped shaking, real steaming barbecue sat inside. One bite told her everything. This wasn't a prank. It was magic. Greed quickly took over. She swapped the paper and requested sushi, and fresh sushi materialized instantly, dish after exotic dish. She pushed the box to its limits and a bold thought hit her. What's the priciest food on earth? A quick search told her caviar, worth nearly $1,000 per spoonful. Her note was full, so she grabbed the nearest item, a supplement box, wrote caviar on it and placed it inside the magic container. the box trembled again and real caviar appeared right before her eyes. She immediately jumped online to brag about tasting such an extravagant delicacy. But midpost, her nose began to bleed, her vision blurred. Moments later, she collapsed, foaming at the mouth. The horrifying truth, the package she wrote on didn't just say supplement It clearly warned poison. The box didn't produce what she wanted. It produced exactly what she wrote on. And this time it killed her.
